<li>A sports club has 12 members. In how many ways can a board consisting of a president, a secretary, and a treasurer (different positions) be chosen?</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> This is a variation (order matters because positions are different): $V_{12,3} = 12 \times 11 \times 10 = \mathbf{1\,320}$ ways.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>EVAU Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>In a chess tournament, 8 players participate. Each pair of players plays exactly one game against each other.</li>
</ol>
<p>a) How many games are played in total?<br />
   b) If the final involves the 2 best from each group of 4, and the two semi-final groups are predetermined, how many games are there in the full format (group stage + semi-finals + final)?<br />
   c) In how many ways can the 8 players finish in the top three places (podium)?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong><br />
a) Each game is a pair of players: $\binom{8}{2} = 28$ games.<br />
b) Groups (2 groups of 4): $2 \times \binom{4}{2} = 2 \times 6 = 12$ games. Semi-finals: 2 games. Final: 1 game. Total: $12 + 2 + 1 = \mathbf{15}$ games.<br />
c) The podium distinguishes 1st, 2nd, 3rd: $V_{8,3} = 8 \times 7 \times 6 = \mathbf{336}$ ways.</p>
</blockquote>
