<h5>10.2.3 Laplace's rule: probability in equiprobable spaces</h5>

<p><strong>Worked Example</strong></p>
<p>A ball is drawn at random from an urn containing 5 red balls, 3 blue balls, and 2 green balls. Calculate the probability of: (a) obtaining a red ball, (b) obtaining a ball that is not blue.</p>
<p><strong>Step-by-step Solution:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Laplace's rule:</strong>
$$P(A) = \frac{\text{favourable cases}}{\text{possible cases}} = \frac{|A|}{|\Omega|}$$</p>
<p>This rule applies because all balls are equally likely (we draw at random).</p>
<p>$|\Omega| = 5 + 3 + 2 = 10$ balls.</p>
<p><strong>(a)</strong> $P(\text{red}) = \dfrac{5}{10} = \mathbf{0{,}5}$</p>
<p><strong>(b)</strong> "Not blue" includes red and green: $5 + 2 = 7$ balls.<br />
$P(\text{not blue}) = \dfrac{7}{10} = \mathbf{0{,}7}$</p>
<p>Verification: $P(\text{blue}) = \dfrac{3}{10} = 0{,}3$ and $P(\text{not blue}) = 1 - 0{,}3 = 0{,}7$. ✓</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Exercises with Solutions</strong></p>
<p><strong>Basic Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
