<p>a) How many ways are there to choose the 2 representatives?<br />
   b) What is the probability that both are men?<br />
   c) What is the probability that there is one woman and one man?<br />
   d) What is the probability that at least one is a woman?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong><br />
a) $\binom{30}{2} = 435$ ways.<br />
b) $P(\text{2 men}) = \dfrac{\binom{18}{2}}{\binom{30}{2}} = \dfrac{153}{435} = \dfrac{51}{145} \approx \mathbf{0{,}352}$.<br />
c) $P(\text{1M+1W}) = \dfrac{18 \times 12}{435} = \dfrac{216}{435} = \dfrac{72}{145} \approx \mathbf{0{,}497}$.<br />
d) $P(\text{at least 1 woman}) = 1 - P(\text{2 men}) = 1 - \dfrac{153}{435} = \dfrac{282}{435} = \dfrac{94}{145} \approx \mathbf{0{,}648}$.</p>
</blockquote>
