<li>A die is rolled. Let $A$ = "even number" and $B$ = "number greater than 3". Calculate $P(A \mid B)$.</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $A = {2,4,6}$, $B = {4,5,6}$, $A \cap B = {4,6}$. $P(A \mid B) = \dfrac{2/6}{3/6} = \dfrac{2}{3} \approx 0{,}667$.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Intermediate Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>In a group of 100 people, 60 speak English, 40 speak French, and 20 speak both languages. A person who speaks English is chosen at random. What is the probability that they also speak French?</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(F \mid I) = \dfrac{P(F \cap I)}{P(I)} = \dfrac{20/100}{60/100} = \dfrac{20}{60} = \dfrac{1}{3} \approx 0{,}333$.</p>
</blockquote>
