<h5>10.5.2 Total probability theorem</h5>

<p><strong>Worked Example</strong></p>
<p>A company has three production lines $L_1$, $L_2$, and $L_3$ that produce 50%, 30%, and 20% of parts respectively. The defect rate of each line is 2%, 4%, and 6%. Calculate the probability that a randomly chosen part is defective.</p>
<p><strong>Step-by-step Solution:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Data:</strong>
$$P(L_1)=0{,}5,\quad P(L_2)=0{,}3,\quad P(L_3)=0{,}2$$
$$P(D \mid L_1)=0{,}02,\quad P(D \mid L_2)=0{,}04,\quad P(D \mid L_3)=0{,}06$$</p>
<p><strong>We verify that ${L_1, L_2, L_3}$ is a partition:</strong>
$P(L_1)+P(L_2)+P(L_3) = 0{,}5+0{,}3+0{,}2 = 1$ ✓</p>
<p><strong>Total probability theorem:</strong>
$$P(D) = P(D \mid L_1) \cdot P(L_1) + P(D \mid L_2) \cdot P(L_2) + P(D \mid L_3) \cdot P(L_3)$$
$$P(D) = 0{,}02 \times 0{,}5 + 0{,}04 \times 0{,}3 + 0{,}06 \times 0{,}2$$
$$P(D) = 0{,}010 + 0{,}012 + 0{,}012 = \mathbf{0{,}034}$$</p>
<p>The probability of a defect is 3.4%.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Exercises with Solutions</strong></p>
<p><strong>Basic Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>There are two urns: $U_1$ with 4 red balls and 6 black balls, $U_2$ with 7 red and 3 black balls. An urn is chosen at random (with equal probability) and a ball is drawn. Calculate the probability of obtaining a red ball.</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(U_1) = P(U_2) = 0{,}5$. $P(R) = P(R \mid U_1) \cdot P(U_1) + P(R \mid U_2) \cdot P(U_2) = \frac{4}{10} \times 0{,}5 + \frac{7}{10} \times 0{,}5 = 0{,}20 + 0{,}35 = \mathbf{0{,}55}$.</p>
</blockquote>
<ol>
<li>A traffic light is green 60% of the time, amber 10%, and red 30%. The probability that a driver stops when the light is green is 0, when amber is 0.7, and when red is 1. Calculate the probability of stopping.</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(\text{stops}) = 0 \times 0{,}6 + 0{,}7 \times 0{,}1 + 1 \times 0{,}3 = 0 + 0{,}07 + 0{,}30 = \mathbf{0{,}37}$.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Intermediate Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>In an educational centre, 60% of students study at home for more than 2 hours per day and 40% study less. Among those who study more than 2 hours, 85% pass; among those who study less, 50% pass. What is the overall pass rate?</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(\text{passes}) = 0{,}85 \times 0{,}6 + 0{,}50 \times 0{,}4 = 0{,}51 + 0{,}20 = \mathbf{0{,}71}$ (71%).</p>
</blockquote>
<ol>
<li>A rapid diagnostic test gives a positive result with probability 0.92 if the person has the disease and with probability 0.05 if they do not. The prevalence of the disease in the population is 2%. Calculate $P(\text{positive test})$.</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(+) = 0{,}92 \times 0{,}02 + 0{,}05 \times 0{,}98 = 0{,}0184 + 0{,}049 = \mathbf{0{,}0674}$.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>EVAU Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>A bank classifies its loans into three categories by risk: low risk (60% of portfolio), medium risk (30%), and high risk (10%). The default rates are 1%, 5%, and 20% respectively.</li>
</ol>
<p>a) Calculate the bank's overall default rate.<br />
   b) If a fourth type of loan with very high risk (15% default) is introduced, replacing 5% of the low-risk portfolio, how does the default rate change?<br />
   c) What maximum weight should high risk carry so that the overall default rate does not exceed 4%?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong><br />
a) $P(\text{default}) = 0{,}01 \times 0{,}6 + 0{,}05 \times 0{,}3 + 0{,}20 \times 0{,}1 = 0{,}006 + 0{,}015 + 0{,}020 = \mathbf{0{,}041}$ (4.1%).<br />
b) New portfolio: Low risk 55%, Medium risk 30%, High 10%, Very high 5%. $P' = 0{,}01 \times 0{,}55 + 0{,}05 \times 0{,}30 + 0{,}20 \times 0{,}10 + 0{,}15 \times 0{,}05 = 0{,}0055+0{,}015+0{,}020+0{,}0075 = \mathbf{0{,}048}$. Increases from 4.1% to 4.8%.<br />
c) Let $x$ be the weight of high risk and $(0{,}6-x+0{,}30)$ the rest. Simplifying with the original portfolio: $0{,}01(0{,}6) + 0{,}05(0{,}3) + 0{,}20x \leq 0{,}04$, with $x + 0{,}9 = 1$, i.e. $x = 0{,}1$ already gives 4.1%. Adjusting with $0{,}6+0{,}3+(x)+(0{,}1-x)=1$: $0{,}006 + 0{,}015 + 0{,}20x \leq 0{,}04 \Rightarrow 0{,}20x \leq 0{,}019 \Rightarrow x \leq \mathbf{0{,}095}$ (9.5%).</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Multiple Choice Test</strong></p>
<ol>
