<li>a) $B$ is any event with no conditions</li>
<li>b) We know $P(B \mid A_i)$ for a partition ${A_i}$ of the sample space</li>
<li>c) $B$ and $A$ are independent</li>
<li>d) $B$ is the complementary event of $A$</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Correct answer: b)</strong> The theorem applies when a partition ${A_1,...,A_n}$ exists and we know $P(B \mid A_i)$ and $P(A_i)$ for each $i$.</p>
