   b) Calculate the probability that a packet weighs more than 1030 g. [$\Phi(2)=0{,}9772$]<br />
   c) Calculate the probability that a packet is within specification.<br />
   d) In a batch of 500 packets, how many are expected to be out of specification?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong><br />
a) $z=(975-1000)/15=-25/15\approx-1{,}67$. $P(X&lt;975)=\Phi(-1{,}67)=1-0{,}9525=\mathbf{0{,}0475}$.<br />
b) $z=(1030-1000)/15=30/15=2$. $P(X&gt;1030)=1-\Phi(2)=1-0{,}9772=\mathbf{0{,}0228}$.<br />
c) $P(975 \leq X \leq 1030)=1-0{,}0475-0{,}0228=\mathbf{0{,}9297}$ (92.97%).<br />
d) $500 \times (1-0{,}9297) = 500 \times 0{,}0703 \approx \mathbf{35{,}15} \approx 35$ packets.</p>
</blockquote>
