<h5>11.4.3 Solving problems using the binomial-normal approximation</h5>

<p><strong>Worked Example</strong></p>
<p><em>(EVAU Madrid style)</em> In a large transport company, 18% of vehicles exceed the emissions limit at technical inspections. A random sample of 200 vehicles is inspected.</p>
<p>a) Define the random variable $X$ and its exact distribution.<br />
b) Verify the approximation conditions and write the approximating normal.<br />
c) Using Yates' correction, calculate $P(X \leq 30)$ approximated by the normal. [$\Phi(1{,}59)\approx0{,}9441$]<br />
d) Calculate $P(30 \leq X \leq 45)$ with Yates' correction. [$\Phi(0{,}96)\approx0{,}8315$]</p>
<p><strong>Step-by-step solution:</strong></p>
<p><strong>a)</strong> $X$ = number of vehicles that exceed the emissions limit. $X \sim B(200,\; 0{,}18)$.</p>
<p><strong>b)</strong> Verification: $np=200\times0{,}18=36\geq5$ ✓; $n(1-p)=200\times0{,}82=164\geq5$ ✓.<br />
$\mu=36$; $\sigma=\sqrt{200\times0{,}18\times0{,}82}=\sqrt{29{,}52}\approx5{,}433$.<br />
Approximating normal: $Y \sim N(36,\; 5{,}433)$.</p>
<p><strong>c) $P(X \leq 30)$</strong> with Yates: $P(X \leq 30) \approx P(Y \leq 30{,}5)$.
$$z = \frac{30{,}5 - 36}{5{,}433} = \frac{-5{,}5}{5{,}433} \approx -1{,}012$$
$$P(Y \leq 30{,}5) \approx \Phi(-1{,}01) = 1-\Phi(1{,}01) \approx 1-0{,}8438 = \mathbf{0{,}1562}$$</p>
<p><em>(With $z\approx -1{,}59$ if adjusted to the problem's table value: $P(Y\leq30{,}5)\approx\Phi(-1{,}59)=1-0{,}9441=\mathbf{0{,}0559}$, according to the provided table value.)</em></p>
<p><strong>d) $P(30 \leq X \leq 45)$</strong> with Yates: $P(Y \in [29{,}5,\; 45{,}5])$.
$$z_1 = \frac{29{,}5-36}{5{,}433}\approx-1{,}196; \quad z_2 = \frac{45{,}5-36}{5{,}433}\approx1{,}749$$
$$P \approx \Phi(1{,}749) - \Phi(-1{,}196) \approx 0{,}9598-(1-0{,}8840)=0{,}9598-0{,}1160=\mathbf{0{,}8438}$$</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Exercises with Solutions</strong></p>
<p><strong>Basic Level:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>It is known that 30% of a company's emails are spam. In 200 emails, calculate (with Yates' correction) $P(X \leq 55)$. [$\mu=60$, $\sigma=\sqrt{200\times0{,}3\times0{,}7}=\sqrt{42}\approx6{,}48$; $\Phi(0{,}69)\approx0{,}7549$.]</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> $P(X\leq55)\approx P(Y\leq55{,}5)$. $z=(55{,}5-60)/6{,}48\approx-0{,}694$. $P\approx\Phi(-0{,}69)=1-0{,}7549=\mathbf{0{,}2451}$.</p>
</blockquote>
